Britannia is an Indian food company established in 1892 in Kolkata. It is now one of the largest food companies in India, with popular brands like Tiger, Good Day, NutriChoice, and Bourbon. Some key milestones in Britannia's history include launching new biscuit brands in the 1950s-1990s that were successful, acquiring other food companies, and establishing plants across India. Today Britannia has a diverse portfolio of biscuits, breads, dairy, cakes, and rusks, selling over 50% of Indian homes.
